description: Jake McCarthy hit a two-out, two-run single down the left-field line in the ninth inning to lift the Arizona Diamondbacks to a 4-3 win over the Colorado Rockies.

headline: Gausman and Guerrero Jr. continue their hot streaks as the Blue Jays beat the Angels 6-1
description: Kevin Gausman tossed seven shutout innings, Vladimir Guerrero Jr. hit his 10th home run since the All-Star break and the Toronto Blue Jays beat the Los Angeles Angels 6-1 on Tuesday night.

headline: Jurors to hear opening statements in trial of ex-politician accused of killing Las Vegas reporter
description: Jurors are set to hear opening statements Wednesday in the murder trial of a Las Vegas-area politician accused of killing investigative reporter Jeff German.

headline: Inflation likely stayed low last month as Federal Reserve edges closer to cutting rates
description: If the Federal Reserve needs any further evidence that the worst price spike in four decades is steadily easing, it’s likely to come Wednesday, when the government is expected to report that inflation cooled further last month.

headline: Olympic women’s silver medalist Vekic knocked off by Krueger, Fritz also upset at Cincinnati Open
description: Donna Vekic was defeated in her first match since winning the silver medal in the Olympics, falling to Ashlyn Krueger 5-7, 7-6 (4), 6-2 on Tuesday at the Cincinnati Open.

headline: House Democrats dig in amid ongoing fight in Congress over compensation for US radiation victims
description: A top Democrat in the U.S. House says it will take a shift of power in Congress to ensure that legislation is finally passed to extend and expand a compensation program for people exposed to radiation following uranium mining and nuclear testing carried out by the federal government.

headline: Soto has 1st career 3-homer game as Yankees beat White Sox 4-1 behind Cortes
description: Juan Soto had his first career three-homer game, Nestor Cortes tossed seven shutout innings and the New York Yankees held off the Chicago White Sox 4-1 to take sole possession of the AL East lead.

headline: Why AP called Minnesota’s 5th District primary for Rep. Ilhan Omar over Don Samuels
description: Rep. Ilhan Omar won the Democratic primary in Minnesota’s 5th Congressional District on Tuesday, defeating former Minneapolis City Council member Don Samuels in a rematch of their close 2022 primary contest.

headline: Shohei Ohtani hits NL-leading 37th homer, Dodgers defeat Brewers 7-2 for 5th straight victory
description: Shohei Ohtani hit his National League-leading 37th home run and the Los Angeles Dodgers finished with four homers in a 7-2 win over the Milwaukee Brewers that extended their winning streak to five games.

headline: Rolling Rookies: Chaparro hits 3 doubles in debut while Wood produces another 4-hit game for Nats
description: James Wood’s first chance to play at Camden Yards was overshadowed by another dandy debut. Andrés Chaparro doubled three times in his first big league game to lead the Washington Nationals to a 9-3 win over the Baltimore Orioles.

headline: Red-hot Langeliers leads A’s to 9-4 win over former teammate Blackburn and skidding Mets
description: Shea Langeliers hit a three-run homer off former batterymate Paul Blackburn and went 4 for 4 again, powering the Oakland Athletics to a 9-4 win over the skidding New York Mets.

headline: Crawford carries perfect game into 6th inning, Wong hits 3-run HR as Red Sox beat Rangers 9-4
description: Kutter Crawford carried a perfect game into the sixth inning and Connor Wong highlighted a 12-hit attack with a three-run homer as the Boston Red Sox beat the slumping Texas Rangers 9-4.

headline: Twins clobber Royals 13-3 to win crisp debut by fast-rising starting pitcher Zebby Matthews
description: Zebby Matthews threw five crisp innings to win his major league debut for the Minnesota Twins, who hit Seth Lugo hard to hand the All-Star right-hander his worst start this season and beat the Kansas City Royals 13-3.

headline: Trump-backed US Rep. Celeste Maloy wins Republican primary in Utah after recount, court case
description: U.S. Rep. Celeste Maloy has narrowly won the Republican primary in Utah’s 2nd District. The state Supreme Court on Tuesday rejected her challenger’s lawsuit that asked justices to count a batch of ballots with late postmarks after Maloy won a recount by fewer than 200 votes.
